<P>
   WALKMAN-20YEARS (Undated) _ Technologically, it was trivial.
Culturally, it was a milestone. Twenty years ago this summer, the
Sony Walkman was introduced in America. From that moment in 1979
the world changed. Look around. They're ubiquitous. By ERIC ADLER.
890 words. Story will move in the ``l'' category.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-BOSTON (BOSTON) It wasn't so long ago that Boston Harbor
was a laughingstock. In the 1988 presidential campaign George Bush
embarrassed rival Michael Dukakis, Massachusetts' governor at the
time, when he called Boston Harbor the dirtiest in America.
</P>
<P>
   Now gleaming new hotels welcome well-heeled guests to the
waterfront. The Temptations, Willie Nelson and Donna Summer brought
yuppie suburbanites to a summer pavilion in the Seaport District. A
federal courthouse opened on Fan Pier last year, and plans call for
a $695 million convention center. Construction is everywhere. By
ALLEN HOLDER. 1,700 words. Story will move in the ``l'' category.
