<P>
   TRAVEL-YMCA (Estes Park, Colo.) _ Benches and Adirondack chairs
they do have at the YMCA of the Rockies meeting center here. And an
awesome view to go with them. And a cafeteria that seats 600. And
an auditorium with chairs for 800. And 530 lodge rooms. And 205
cabins set back in the fringes.
</P>
<P>
   Although most of the facilities were built decades ago to
accommodate conferences of church members and young people, school
and recreational groups, in more recent years this has become a
magnet for grannies and grandpas, aunts and uncles, siblings,
grandchildren and cousins.
</P>
<P>
   The YMCA's Estes Park Center, and its sister center, Snow
Mountain Ranch near Winter Park, Colo., now find themselves in the
family-reunion business. And a booming business it has proven to
be. By KAREN UHLENHUTH. 1,500 words. Story will move in the ``l''
category.
</P>
<P>
   CLASSICAL-REVIEW (Undated) _ Summertime, when in most cities the
concert schedule slows to a crawl, is a good time for settling into
an easy chair, enjoying the air conditioning and catching up on
recordings. Here's a rundown of recent CDs of note, including
several outstanding reissues. By SCOTT CANTRELL. 1,300 words. Story
will move in the ``e'' category.
