<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   HAZING _ WASHINGTON _ The results of the nation's first
comprehensive survey of hazing in college sports are released at a
press conference Monday. (Mollison, Cox News Service). 25.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   DENNIS _ The punch-packing heart of Hurricane Dennis continued
to track parallel to the North Carolina coast today, while its edge
brought pelting rain, strong winds and the threat of beachfront
flooding. (Burritt, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-LAWSUIT _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Attorneys for Gov. George W. Bush
were in court Monday morning in an attempt to prevent him from
being dragged into a whistleblower lawsuit involving the former
executive director of the funeral commission, who was fired in the
middle of an investigation into a funeral home company owned by a
Bush contributor. (Elizondo, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-SMUGGLING _ ATLANTA _ Immigrant smuggling from Asia has
become big business in the last 10 years. We've seen recent cases
where Asian women promised a better life were smuggled to USA to
work as prositutes to pay off their debts. And more than 130
Chinese endured weeks at sea in poor conditions to get here. Why do
people pay up to $50,000 - dozens of times their annual income in
China - to endure slave-ship conditions to come here? Do they know
they'll end up in sweatshops, brothel or Chinese restaurants?
(Bixler, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30.
</P>
<P>
   w/ASIAN-PROSTITUTES _ ATLANTA _ For five years, four separate
organizations _ one of them a Chinese tong _ ran houses of
prostitution in suburban Atlanta, which they stocked with young
women from Viet Nam, Thailand, Korea, Malaysia and China. The
women, many of them teenagers, were, for all intents and purposes,
slaves. Smuggled into the U.S. for prices between $35,000 and
$40,000 a piece by men known as snakeheads, the women worked for
$100 a customer. Of that money, $30 would go to the brothel where
they were kept under armed guard (often houses or apartments
furnished only with mattresses and condoms). The remainder repaid
the men snakeheads, the jockeys and agents who had smuggled them
into the country and arranged for false identities. Johns were
often recruited from metro Chinese restaurants, including one whose
owner, was prosecuted for organized gambling three years ago and
whose girlfriend is a suspected madam. (McDonald, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 45.
</P>
<P>
   UGA-LAWSUIT _ATLANTA _ Attorney Lee Parks has found three white,
females to file a class action lawsuit against the University of
Georgia for racial and gender discrimination. The women claim they
were not admitted because of their gender and race. Parks' last
client, Jennifer Johnson, was admitted into UGA, although she is
now at Mercer. (Suggs, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   SCHOOL-CIVILITY _ ATLANTA _ Students, it seems, aren't the only
ones occasionally acting up in Fayette County schools. Adults are
too, school officials say. They're getting too rowdy at sporting
events, yelling during meetings with teachers and even cursing in
classrooms. In hopes of curbing this misbehavior, the district is
drafting a ``civility policy'' outlining what is expected of school
visitors. The policy would not have any teeth _ no punishment faces
parents or others who violate the new code. Fayette Superintendent
John DeCotis said he's hoping that simply spelling out what is
appropriate behavior for visitors should do the trick. (Donsky,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   SCIENCE-MEDICINEAIDS-CONFERENCE _ ATLANTA _ AIDS deaths are
still declining, but far more slowly than they were two years ago,
according to new national data released by the CDC Monday at the
National HIV Prevention Conference. Researchers say the slowing
decline is probably due to a combination of factors, including the
development of HIV drug resistance. (Kim, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   w/AIDSBLACKS _ ATLANTA _ In 1998, AIDS death rates and infection
rates were nearly 10 times higher among African Americans than
among whites. Infection rates are especially high among black gay
and bisexual men and black drug users. In response, the CDC is
continuing to expand its HIV prevention programs in
African-American communities. (Kim, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   YUGOSLAVIA-OPPOSITION _ BELGRADE, Yugoslavia _ NATO's
devastating air-bombardment campaign rearranged entire landscapes
at ground level, but a couple of facts important to Serbia's
beleaguered and frustrated democratic opposition remain firmly in
place. First, Yugoslav president Slobodan Milosevic, still rules.
And second, the Clinton Administration's policy of using economic
isolation and bare humanitarian assistance to force Milosevic's
removal hasn't budged. (Jolidon, Cox News Service) M0VED.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   YUGOSLAVIA-BOX _ A thumbnail box of Serb Democratic opposition
leaders. (Jolidon, Cox News Service) MOVED.
