<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-30 14:11 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A4475 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u e BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS &LR;      08-30 0394
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EVEN ON DVD, `TITANIC' IS SOS (SAME OLD STORY) 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Titanic'' (DVD) _ How many times can they float
this movie? Now it's on DVD, but there are no extra bells and
whistles. They'll probably release the extra features on a future
DVD release. The next time you need a synonym for cash cow, use
``Titanic.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Cleopatra'' _ Not Elizabeth Taylor and Richard Burton. Not
worth it.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Doctor Is In'' _ These episodes of ``The Bob Newhart
Show,'' the one in which Newhart is a psychiatrist, are splendid.
The stone-faced master of the double take is one of the best
situation-comedy comics to ever grace the small screen.
</P>
<P>
   PBS VHS: In mid-September, around the time the 10-part ``An
American Love Story'' premieres on PBS, New Video will release the
series in five volumes for $99.95. The documentary covers two years
in the life of an interracial family. Yes, it's long. But worth
every minute. It might even dissuade viewers from thinking every
show must be paced like an MTV video.
</P>
<P>
   New Video has also slated two other nonfiction titles for fall
release _ ``Off the Menu: The Last Days of Chasen's,'' set during
the legendary Beverly Hills restaurant's final week, and ``Climb
Against the Odds,'' a moving story of cancer patients climbing
mountains.
</P>
<P>
   DVD UPDATE: According to the International Recording Media
Association's latest survey, by 2003 there will be 24.6 million DVD
players sold internationally.
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Sept. 7: ``The Other Sister'' (DVD),
``Mary-Kate and Ashley's Fashion Party,'' ``Deep Crimson,'' ``Park
City: The Vanguard Collection,'' ``Twin Dragons'' (DVD), ``The
Crow: Stairway to Heaven.'' Sept. 14: ``Cookie's Fortune,''
``Children of Heaven,'' ``The Snow of Winter,'' ``The Prince of
Egypt'' (DVD), ``All Creatures Great and Small,'' ``God Said Ha!,''
``Children of Heaven.'' Sept. 21: ``My Favorite Martian,''
``Labyrinth,'' ``Atomic Train,'' ``The Dark Crystal,'' ``Lulu on
the Bridge.'' Sept. 28: ``The Mummy'' (DVD), ``Alvin and the
Chipmunks Meet Frankenstein,'' ``My Favorite Martian'' (DVD). Oct.
5: ``Lolita'' (1999 version), ``Scooby-Doo and the Witch's Ghost.''
Oct. 19: ``The Wizard of Oz'' (remastered and DVD). Oct. 31: ``The
Blair Witch Project.''
</P>
