   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TIMOR-VOTE (Dili, East Timor) _ East Timorese vote in massive
numbers on a day that turns out far less violent than feared, an
indication that the vote will almost surely favor independence.
While one local UN worker is killed and two others wounded in an
attack, UN officials heave a sigh of relief. By Indira A.R.
Lakshmanan. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   HAZING-SURVEY (Washington) _ Results of the first comprehensive
survey of hazing in college sports, sponsored by Alfred University
in New York and the NCAA. By Eun Lee Koh. 750 words. (w and a
coding)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   AIDS-DECLINE (Undated) _ While the number of AIDS deaths
continues to drop, the rapid rate of decline that had been
attributed to new AIDS drugs is starting to slow dramatically, US
public health officials say. By Dolores Kong. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS (e) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TV-FORD (Undated) _ Jack Ford, ``Today'' show weekend anchor
will go to ABC, where he'll be anchor-in-waiting for the ``Good
Morning America'' male slot when Charles Gibson steps down. By Don
Aucoin. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ATT-RATES (Undated) _ AT&AMP;T strikes back at rivals' cheaper phone
rates by cutting prices for long-distance calls to 7 cents a
minute, plus $5.95 a month. But what AT&AMP;T touts as a simpler plan
than competing offers of 5 cents a minute may muddy the already
befuddling process of picking which rate is best for you. By Peter
Howe. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   ALPHA-CHIP (Undated) _ What happened to Alpha Processor Inc.
last week would be the kiss of death for many computer firms. But
nobody's hanging any crepe at Alpha, even though it's just learned
that the world's biggest software company is abandoning it. By
Hiawatha Bray. 800 words.
</P>
