<HEADLINE>
TRAVELING THE NET 
</HEADLINE>
   (For release Sun., Sept. 5)  
(jt) 
 By JANET PIORKO   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRISH AUTUMN _ CIE Tours International is offering seven-night
driving trips to Ireland from Oct. 16 to Dec. 13, then again in
January and February, starting at $591 a person, double occupancy,
including air fare from New York. The price includes use of a
minimum-category rental car with unlimited mileage for a week;
seven nights' lodging with private bath at farmhouses and town and
country homes; full Irish breakfast daily, local taxes and service
charges, and a discount booklet for visitor attractions. A similar
package including hotel accommodations with private bath or shower
starts at $717; the company also has four-night escorted bus tours
starting at $799, including air fare, with various departures from
November through March. Information: (800) 243-8687.
</P>
<P>
   WEEK IN KYOTO _ TBI Tours and United Airlines are offering a
six-night Price Buster Kyoto program from late January through
mid-March of next year for $999 a person, double occupancy, from
the West Coast ($60 more from elsewhere in the United States). In
addition to the round-trip air fare to Osaka, it includes six
nights at the New Miyako Hotel, a day of sightseeing with lunch,
airport transfers, service charges and hotel taxes. A two-night
stay in Tokyo can be added for $435. Information or reservations:
(800) 223-0266.
</P>
<P>
   WORK AND PLAY _ Guests who can stay for at least three weeks and
are willing to work one day a week can get a 30 percent discount on
a winter stay at Maho Bay Camps and Estate Concordia, two of the
ecologically oriented Maho Bay Resorts on St. John in the United
States Virgin Islands. Housekeeping, cooking and gardening are some
possible tasks. The offer is good Dec. 1 through April 30. Winter
rates start at $105 a night for one or two guests in a tent
cottage. In a separate off-season program, the resort has been
offering free lodging to guests who work at Maho Bay Camps for four
hours each day. Information: (800) 392-9004; on the Internet:
www.maho.org.
</P>
<P>
   SEAGOING SAVINGS _ The Seven Seas Navigator, the new
490-passenger ship of Radisson Seven Seas Cruises, is offering
two-for-one savings on its nine-night Atlantic crossing from
Madeira to Fort Lauderdale departing Oct. 9. The ship is scheduled
to enter service Sept. 7. With the discount, the total fare for two
people in a cabin would start at $5,595, which includes air fare
from the East Coast.
</P>
<P>
   The line also offers a two-for-one saving on a 10-night cruise
on Dec. 17 from Puntarenas, Costa Rica, to San Juan on the
350-passenger Radisson Diamond. With the saving, the fare for two
people in a cabin would start at $5,795, including air fare. On
other Panama Canal and Costa Rica cruises, the company has
discounts of up to 50 percent for a second passenger in a cabin if
reservations are made by Sept. 15. Information: (800) 285-1835.
</P>
