   RAPE-SENTENCE (Los Angeles) _ Sentenced in Van Nuys Superior
Court Monday to 20 consecutive life terms for a series of rapes,
Carlos Rodriguez won't be eligible for parole for 990 years. It's
the longest sentence in anyone's memory and may be a record for
California. By Jesse Hiestand. (Will move in the ``n'' California
and ``a'' national news file.)
</P>
<P>
   RAVE-CRASH (Los Angeles) _ U.S. Forest Service and Los Angeles
County Sheriff's Department officials were meeting Monday to
discuss the investigation into the deaths of four San Bernardino
high school students and a recent graduate as their car careened
down a steep slope off the Angeles Crest Highway after a rave party
at a ski resort. By Lisa Van Proyen and Harrison Sheppard. (Will
move in the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   SCHOOL-SAFE (Los Angeles) _ With campus shootings capturing the
nation's attention, the Los Angeles Police Department has begun
training Los Angeles Unified School District officials in the
techniques of threat assessment to head off a potential Columbine
shooting here. But at the 11th annual ``Safe Return to Schools''
meeting Monday at the LAPD Academy in Elysian Park, police and
school officials emphasized another even greater safety concern:
traffic. By Douglas Haberman. (Will move in the ``n'' California
news file.)
</P>
<P>
   FURROW-TRIAL (Los Angeles) _ An October 12 trial date was set
Monday for Buford O'Neal Furrow, Jr., on federal murder and weapons
charges in the slaying of Filipino-American postal worker Joseph
Ileto after the shooting attack at the North Valley Jewish
Community Center. By Michael Coit. (Will move in the ``n''
California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   ARCO-MERGER (Los Angeles) _ Arco shareholders overwhelmingly
approved a proposed merger with British petroleum giant BP Amoco
Monday, but several key questions remain about the merger's effect
on Arco's Los Angeles headquarters and the company's 3,000
employees in the region. By Jason Takenouchi.
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in the ``f'' financial and ``n'' California news
file.)
</P>
