<P>
   FED-STOCKS (Jackson Hole, Wyo.) _ The Federal Reserve's annual
two-day gathering at Jackson Lake Lodge has evolved from an
informal get-together for central bankers into a high-powered forum
for debating the issues that shape economies around the world. The
big topic this year was the ever-rising American stock market. By
Louis Uchitelle.
</P>
<P>
   (The story is scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   SPLURGE-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ Amid the market's record highs
and volatile moves, many investors have decided to sell some of
their funds and use the profit to remodel the bathroom, buy a new
washing machine, take that expensive vacation or splurge in some
way. Investors are cashing out mutual fund shares at the highest
rate in almost a dozen years. By Richard A. Oppel Jr.
</P>
<P>
