<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Weather Channel site promotes three execs
 &HT;    By Charles Haddad
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Weather.com, the online service of the Weather
Channel, has promoted three of its top executives, the company
announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Debora Wilson has been named Weather.com's president and chief
executive. Todd Walrath was named chief operating officer and Paul
Iaffaldano chief revenue officer.
</P>
<P>
   All executives have played key roles in the development of
Weather.com, one of the Internet's leading weather sites.
</P>
<P>
   ``Weather.com's status as a leading Web site and premier
advertising destination is largely the result of the outstanding
leadership and strategic abilities demonstrated by Debora, Todd and
Paul,'' said Decker Anstrom, president and chief executive of the
Atlanta-based Weather Channel, which produces weather.com. The
Weather Channel is a private company owned by Landmark
Communications.
</P>
<P>
   Wilson has held various positions at the Weather Channel. Her
most recent job was as executive vice president and general manager
of online services.
</P>
<P>
   Walrath also has long been involved with Weather.com. In his
previous position, Walrath was senior vice president of online
services and oversaw content and business development.
</P>
<P>
   Iaffaldano was vice president of online advertising sales. In
his new job, he will continuing leading Weather.com's sales force.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
