sweater with a giant cowl and tweed cuffed trousers, all by John
Galliano, also at Neiman Marcus. (Marilynn K. Yee/New York Times
Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT23) NEW YORK -- Aug. 30, 1999 -- CLOSING-HURLEY'S, 08-30 --
Hurley's restaurant, at the corner of 49th Street and Sixth Avenue,
on Monday, top, and as Rockefeller Center was constructed around it
in the 1930's. For decades, Hurley's restaurant bucked the odds.
When Prohibition came, the Hurley brothers put a flower shop in
front to hide the speakeasy. When Rockefeller Center was built, the
family stubbornly refused to sell their property, forcing the
developers to build the huge complex around them. But now, it
appears, Hurley's days are coming to end. With more stylish tenants
moving in around them, the restaurant's owners have decided to
close. The restaurant will be replaced by Citarella's, the upscale
food store, according someone familiar with the deal who spoke on
condition of anonymity. (Chester Higgins Jr./New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT22) NEW YORK -- Aug. 30, 1999 -- NY-GIULIANI-JUROR, 08-30 --
Mayor Rudolph Giuliani, a former federal prosecutor, was selected
to serve on jury duty Monday. The civil case involves a man named
Oliver Johnson who is suing his landlord because he scalded his
private parts while taking a shower. Giuliani is seen in a 1998
file photo. (Ruby Washington/New York Times Photo)
</P>
